    "We show that such a pretraining approach leads to faster convergence and higher predictive power on all of the mentioned tasks with limited annotated datasets.",
    "We also find that fine-tuning with pretrained weights helps smaller and architecturally simpler models achieve similar or even higher scores compared to training with random weight initialization.",
    "Materials and Methods HRTEM Au DatasetThe Gold nanoparticle image dataset consists of high-and low-resolution TEM images of Gold (Au) nanoparticles with varying sizes (2.2 nm, 5 nm, 10 nm, and 20 nm) and different surface ligands, i.e., citrate (for 2.2 nm) and tannic acid.",
    "The images were acquired using an aberrationcorrected TEAM 0.5 TEM for 2.2, 5, and 10 nm nanoparticles, while low-resolution images of 20 nm nanoparticles were obtained with a non-aberration-corrected TitanX TEM.",
    "The nanoparticles have a different crystalline structure than the embedding matrix (which is amorphous)."
